Point Lights work much like a real world light bulb, emitting light in all directions from the light bulb's tungsten filament.

Rect Lights emit light into the scene from a rectangular plane with a defined width and height. Rect lights are particularly great as key lights due to the fine-tuned control over the source.

Spot Lights emit light from a single point in a cone shape.
